<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-07T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-07T13:00:00-05:00" n="913" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d913">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 PW/7–745: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-07T14:00:00-04:00">July 7,
                                    1945—2 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1128. In conversation yesterday Tarchiani said Italian Govt had decided
                            to declare war against Japan. In reply to his inquiry as to when
                            announcement should be made, he was told this must be determined by Ital
                            Govt but that we hoped it would be soon.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>